{
  "texts": [
    "Navigating Spreading-out Graph (NSG) [54], similarly to DPG, builds an approximate k-NNG first.",
    "But, unlike DPG, it builds an EFANNA graph rather than a KGraph.",
    "It then diversifies the graph using RND.",
    "At the end, NSG creates a depth-first search tree to verify the connectivity of the graph.",
    "If there is a vertex that is disconnected from the tree, NSG connects it to the nearest node in the tree to ensure graph connectivity.SPTAG [29] is a library for approximate vector search proposed by Microsoft."
  ]
}